  "text": "In the propofol group, HR, systolic blood pressure (SBP), and diastolic blood pressure (DBP) significantly increased at the time of extubation (T3) in contrast to dexmedetomidine-sedated patients who manifested non-significant changes in SBP and DBP (P>0.05). Dexmedetomidine sedation decreased the HR significantly after its initiation and was significantly less than in the propofol group. Oxygen saturation decreased and ETCO 2 increased at 30 min after propofol initiation. The SPO 2 and ETCO [CITATION_1] were not changed in the dexmedetomidine group (both P<0.05, in comparison with the propofol group). BIS values were significantly lower in the dexmedetomidine group than in the propofol group at Ramsay sedation scores of 4 and 5 (P=0.045).",
